South Africa Inflation-Linked Bond Yields Rise at Auction

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-09-30T09:19:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/south-africa-inflation-linked-bond-yields-rise-at-auction.html
Yields of  South Africa ’s inflation-
linked bonds rose at an auction of the debt today, according to
the Pretoria-based Reserve Bank’s data on Bloomberg.  The central bank sold 155 million rand of notes due 2022 at
an average yield of 2.47 percent, two basis points higher than
at the previous auction on Sept. 27. It sold 215 million rand of
bonds due 2028 at a yield of 2.54 percent, and 230 million rand
of securities due 2033 at a yield of 2.54 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Robert Brand at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net  